  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting Older People headed households from COVID-19 through community-based health systems strengthening and food security initiatives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will target 2500 households headed by older people in Bebedo, Nhamboca, Ndeja and Metochira Ressetlemnt Sites communities of Nhamatanda district and Mutua and Chinamcondo communities in Dondo district. The intervention is planned to strengthen linkage and coordination of community level structures with the health systems in the process of mitigating and responding to COVID-19 through: 
1) Strengthening the capacity of older people structures that HelpAge has successfully developed in order to address the information gaps on COVID-19; promote referral linkages of suspected cases (HBCs will be linked with the formal health systems; and address isolation, psychosocial trauma and fear among older people.  
2) To strengthen health system responses by influencing the National COVID-19 response to ensure issues of COVID-19 combined with other conditions are observed in the GoM response plan and fully addressed; 
3) Direct support to older people who are self-isolating through food item distributions and provision of transport at the sufficient time to move to market to get supplies ahead of any quarantine as will be agreed with the government. 
4) Provide HelpAge and partner staff with clear guidance on health awareness through training and capacity development sessions; and provision of PPE safety equipment gear for COVID-19.</narrative>
  </description>
